## Column Definition Patterns

### Explicit colId Required

Every column MUST have an explicit `colId` to prevent the phantom column bug:

```python
# CORRECT - explicit colId prevents "Name 3", "Sort Key 2" bug
column_defs = [
    {
        "field": "name",
        "colId": "name",  # REQUIRED
        "headerName": "Name",
        "sortable": True,
    },
    {
        "field": "project_name",
        "colId": "project_name",  # REQUIRED
        "headerName": "Project",
        "sortable": True,
    },
]

# WRONG - missing colId causes phantom columns
column_defs = [
    {"field": "name", "headerName": "Name"},  # NO colId!
]
```

### Boolean Columns - Prevent Auto-Checkbox

Boolean fields automatically render as checkboxes. Add `cellDataType: False` to prevent this:

```python
{
    "field": "is_active",
    "colId": "is_active",
    "headerName": "Active",
    "cellDataType": False,  # Prevents unwanted checkbox
    ":valueFormatter": "params => params.value ? '✓ Yes' : ''",
}
```

### Runtime Column Updates

Never mutate options directly. Use the API:

```python
# WRONG - changes won't appear
grid.options["columnDefs"] = new_col_defs
grid.update()

# CORRECT - use AG Grid API
async def update_columns(grid, new_col_defs):
    await grid.run_grid_method("setGridOption", "columnDefs", new_col_defs)
```

