## Layout and Container Patterns

### CSS Grid for Proper Sizing

AG Grid needs explicit height. Use CSS Grid layout:

```python
with ui.element("div").style(
    "display: grid; "
    "grid-template-rows: auto 1fr; "  # Toolbar auto, grid fills rest
    "width: 100%; "
    "height: 100%; "
    "gap: 8px; "
    "overflow: hidden;"
):
    # Toolbar row (auto height)
    with ui.row().classes("w-full items-center gap-2"):
        ui.input(placeholder="Search...").props("outlined dense clearable")
        ui.button("Export CSV", icon="download")
    
    # Grid container (fills remaining space)
    grid_container = ui.element("div").classes("w-full h-full").style(
        "min-height: 200px;"
    )
    
    with grid_container:
        grid = ui.aggrid({...}, theme="quartz").classes("w-full h-full ag-theme-quartz-auto-dark")
```

### Grid Container Rebuild Pattern

When columns change significantly, rebuild the entire grid:

```python
grid_container = ui.element("div").classes("w-full h-full").style("min-height: 200px;")
grid_ref = {"grid": None}

def build_grid_in_container():
    column_defs = build_column_defs()
    row_data = get_filtered_data()
    
    grid = ui.aggrid({
        "columnDefs": column_defs,
        "rowData": row_data,
        ...
    }, theme="quartz").classes("w-full h-full ag-theme-quartz-auto-dark")
    
    grid_ref["grid"] = grid
    grid.on("cellClicked", handle_cell_click)

def rebuild_grid():
    grid_container.clear()
    with grid_container:
        build_grid_in_container()

# Initial grid creation
with grid_container:
    build_grid_in_container()
```

### Height Patterns

```python
# Fill available space (recommended)
grid = ui.aggrid({...}).classes("w-full h-full").style("overflow-x: auto;")

# Fixed height
grid = ui.aggrid({...}).classes("w-full").style("height: 400px;")

# Flex-grow in flex container
grid = ui.aggrid({...}).classes("w-full flex-grow").style(
    "height: 100%; min-height: 300px;"
)
```

