## Styling Patterns

### valueFormatter for Display Text

Use `:valueFormatter` (colon prefix) for JavaScript functions:

```python
{
    "field": "action",
    "colId": "action",
    "headerName": "Action",
    ":valueFormatter": """params => {
        const labels = {
            'match': '⛓️ Match',
            'create_new': '➕ Create New',
            'skip': '⏭️ Skip',
        };
        return labels[params.value] || params.value;
    }""",
}
```

### cellClassRules for Conditional Styling

Prefer `cellClassRules` over `cellRenderer` for NiceGUI compatibility:

```python
{
    "field": "status",
    "colId": "status",
    "headerName": "Status",
    ":valueFormatter": """params => {
        const labels = {
            'pending': '⏳ Pending',
            'confirmed': '✓ Confirmed',
            'error': '✗ Error',
        };
        return labels[params.value] || params.value;
    }""",
    "cellClassRules": {
        "status-pending": "x === 'pending'",
        "status-confirmed": "x === 'confirmed'",
        "status-error": "x === 'error'",
    },
}
```

### Row Class Rules

```python
grid_options = {
    "rowClassRules": {
        "row-confirmed": "data.status === 'confirmed'",
        "row-error": "data.status === 'error'",
        "row-skipped": "data.action === 'skip'",
    },
}
```

### Dark Mode CSS

Always define both light and dark mode variants:

```python
ui.add_css("""
    /* Light mode */
    .status-pending { color: #D97706 !important; }
    .status-confirmed { color: #059669 !important; font-weight: 600; }
    .status-error { color: #DC2626 !important; font-weight: 600; }
    
    .row-confirmed { background-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15) !important; }
    .row-error { background-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.15) !important; }
    
    /* Dark mode - brighter colors for visibility */
    .dark .status-pending, .body--dark .status-pending { color: #FCD34D !important; }
    .dark .status-confirmed, .body--dark .status-confirmed { color: #6EE7B7 !important; }
    .dark .status-error, .body--dark .status-error { color: #FCA5A5 !important; }
    
    .dark .row-confirmed, .body--dark .row-confirmed {
        background-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.25) !important;
    }
    .dark .row-error, .body--dark .row-error {
        background-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.25) !important;
    }
""")
